  "local_port": 54422,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "My Instagram account with 8.5k followers just got hacked into. I've spent the the last hour looking up ways to hack it and trying to get it back and nothing's working. How can I get it back?",
  "response": "I'm sorry to hear about your situation. Recovering a hacked Instagram account can be stressful, but here are some steps you can take to try to regain access:\n\n1. **Immediate Actions:**\n   - Attempt to reset your password by selecting \"Forgot password?\" on the Instagram login page. Use your email address, phone number, or Facebook account (if linked) to reset the password.\n   - Check your email account for any messages from Instagram regarding changes to your account information. If you received a message about a change you didn\u2019t make, use the \u201crevert this change\u201d option in the email.\n\n2. **Secure Your Email Account:**\n   - Ensure that the email account associated with your Instagram is secure. Change the password if necessary, and enable two-factor authentication (2FA).\n\n3. **Report to Instagram:**\n   - Go to the Instagram Help Center (help.instagram.com) and navigate to the \"Privacy & Safety Center.\"\n   - Select \"Report Something\" and then \"Hacked Accounts\" to fill out a form detailing your issue.\n   - Alternatively, use the following recovery form link: https://www.instagram.com/hacked. Follow the prompts to report the account as hacked.\n\n4. **Use Two-Factor Authentication:**\n   - Once you regain access, enable two-factor authentication for extra security long-term.\n\n5. **Check Devices and Sessions:**\n   - If you manage to log back into your account, navigate to \"Settings\" > \"Security\" > \"Login Activity\" to check for unknown devices or locations. Log out of any you don\u2019t recognize.\n\n6. **Contact Instagram Support:**\n   - If the previous steps aren\u2019t successful, consider reaching out to Instagram Support via their official social media channels for further assistance.\n\nRemember to stay vigilant in the future, and be cautious with suspicious emails or messages that ask for personal information.",
